The paper deals with the problem of searching in trees, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of mobile agents and the optimization of search strategies suggest that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The problem of connected searching in trees is also related to graph algorithms and computational geometry, which are covered by the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm for a specific case of the problem, which may be of interest to researchers in the field of Structural Informatics (cs.SI).
